---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Community Map"
  description="A coming-soon aggregated, anonymized community health map for Ladera Ranch and other California communities."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-10 sm:py-14">
    <p class="font-display text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-gold-700">
      Coming soon
    </p>
    <h1 class="mt-3 font-display text-4xl font-semibold leading-tight text-oak-900 sm:text-5xl">
      Community Map
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-oak-700">
      We're building a map to show self-reported health data at a community level. It isn't ready
      yet. Here's exactly what it will and won't show once it launches.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-8 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="border border-oak-700/25 bg-paper-50 p-6">
        <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-oak-900">What it will show</h2>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-base leading-relaxed text-oak-700">
          <li>Aggregated, anonymized counts, for example by community village or zip code</li>
          <li>Primary coverage of Orange County, with room for reports from other California communities</li>
          <li>Trends over time, once there's enough aggregated data to show them responsibly</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-oak-700/25 bg-paper-50 p-6">
        <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-oak-900">What it will never show</h2>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-base leading-relaxed text-oak-700">
          <li>Individual homes or streets</li>
          <li>Any information that could identify a specific person or family</li>
          <li>Case counts small enough, combined with other details, to identify someone</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-8 border-l-2 border-oak-700/30 pl-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-oak-900">
      This promise isn't just a design choice: it's a condition of building the map at all. If we
      can't aggregate a data point without risking someone's privacy, we won't display it.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-8 text-base leading-relaxed text-oak-700">
      Want to help build it, or have mapping/GIS experience? See
      <a href="/get-involved/" class="text-fog-700 underline">Get Involved</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
